        "title": "feat(nomad): add delegated-run provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add the Nomad delegated-run provider with config, doctor, job lifecycle, allocation exec run support, archive sync, list/status/stop/cleanup, and provider registration.\n- Add Nomad provider docs, command docs, metadata/matrix updates, and live smoke dispatcher coverage.\n- Fix closeout review findings for unclaimed job cleanup, missing-claim cleanup, unsupported run-session handles, unix socket addresses, and untrusted repository config credential redirection.\n- Include a focused Apple VZ readiness-timeout fix found while stabilizing the full verification suite.\n\nCloses #380.\n\n## Verification\n- `go test ./internal/providers/nomad -run 'Run|Unix|Config|WarmupCleans|CleanupRemoves'`\n- `go test ./internal/providers/nomad ./internal/providers/all ./internal/cli`\n- `go test ./...`\n- `go vet ./...`\n- `node scripts/generate-provider-matrix.mjs --check`\n- `bash scripts/check-docs.sh`\n- `bash -n scripts/live-nomad-smoke.sh`\n- `node --test scripts/live-nomad-smoke.test.js`\n- `node --test scripts/live-smoke.test.js`\n- `go build -trimpath -o bin/crabbox ./cmd/crabbox`\n- `bin/crabbox providers --json`\n- `bin/crabbox providers filters --json`\n- `scripts/live-nomad-smoke.sh` classified non-live run as `environment_blocked` with reason `CRABBOX_LIVE_not_enabled`.\n\n## Review Notes\n- Codex autoreview found actionable Nomad lifecycle/run-session/unix-address/config-trust issues; all were fixed in follow-up commits.\n- Final Codex autoreview rerun was quota-blocked after the fix. OpenCode fallback review was auth-blocked, so the PR includes green automated verification plus the fixed earlier review findings, but not a clean final AI-review rerun.\n",
